description.1: When Loki realizes the complications that go along with bringing the ancient DESTROYER back to Earth, he tries to stop the worst from happening! Too little, too late!
description.2: THE BLITZ SQUAD STRIKES! Baron Strucker and his Blitzkrieg Squad take control of a prison in Scotland and it's up to Fury and his men to reclaim it.
description.3: Uatu the Watcher comes from an immortal race, but even HE needs the help of the Fantastic Four!
description.4: As Pepper Potts chews Iron Man out for Happy Hogan's departure, Happy himself is taking a one way trip to Shannon, Ireland to get away from his life at Stark Industries.
description.6: Daredevil continues to fight alongside the FF in defense of the Baxter Building. Will the super team be rudely evicted from their home...by Doctor Doom?
description.7: Who is the mysterious Crime-Master and how does he know the Green Goblin's true identity? And just what are their plans for the Amazing Spider-Man?
description.8: Reprinting Journey Into Mystery Annual (1965) #1, available in MU!
description.14: While searching for Loki's enchanted Norn Stones, Thor as Donald Blake is captured by the Viet Cong army!
description.15: While on furlough, Sgt. Fury decides to seek revenge on General Von Krummpt, the Nazi officer who ordered the raid that killed Pamela Hawley.
description.16: The Puppet Master is back! But for some reason he looks a bit different this time...
description.17: Daredevil and the FF! The blind super hero won't need his sight to lead the team. But why have the superheroes combined forces? Is it because of Doctor Doom's ominous return?
description.22: Hawkeye, Scarlet Witch and Quicksilver join the Avengers for the first time!  Following the consequences of their battle with The Masters of Evil, the Avengers' roster changes dramatically! Who will stay? Who will go? It's the start of a great new Avengers line-up!
description.23: Loki plays dirty during the obstacles in the Trial of the Gods, even going as far as unleashing the Enchantress and Skurge on Jane Foster!
description.24: Just when he is ready to ask Pamela to marry him, Fury and his Commandos must go on a mission to sink a German ship. Sudden death claims another victim...who will it be?
description.25: The Fantastic Four embark on an interstellar mission!
description.26: US Senator Harrington Byrd has commissioned Stark Industries to build a new submarine, which is to be tested by Iron Man.
description.28: The Frightful Four return, and this time they've brought their A-game. The villains have managed to strand the FF without resources! Are the Fantastic Four truly defeated?
description.32: Don’t waste a minute! You’ve got to see Spidey in action against the Goblin and the Gangsters!
description.34: Realizing that weapons and force are no way to defeat the Absorbing Man, Thor uses his creativity and control over the elements to battle his new foe.
description.35: WHILE THE JUNGLE SLEEPS! The Commandos must rescue an American unit lost in the jungle.
description.36: A simple bank robbery may be a part of a grand conspiracy. Who else is behind this but the Mad Thinker!
description.37: In their exploration, the Fantastic Four have ended up on a distant planet in a remote galaxy. But when they encounter the natives will the meeting be friendly...or sinister? A galactic adventure that opens a new can of worms for the super team!
description.43: New thrills! New villains! New surprises! Spider-Man takes on the Clown and his Masters of Menace!
description.44: Behold! The Absorbing Man's first appearance! Loki bestows an enchantment upon commonplace criminal, Carl Creel.
description.45: The Howling Commandos are sent to North Africa to uncover the Nazis' current project.
description.46: The Beatles, yes THOSE Beatles, make their first ever appearance in a Marvel comic! Meet Paul, John, Ringo and George...in the Mighty Marvel treatment!
description.48: The Frightful Four versus the Fantastic Four! The Wizard! Medusa! Sand Man! Trapster! Will the FF be overpowered by the brawn and brains of their toughest foes yet?
description.54: At last! Don Blake feels he is ready to admit his true identity as THOR to Jane Foster, but is he ready to face the consequences from Odin?
description.55: Agent X calls for a strike against a Nazi gathering on the shores of Holland and The Howling Commandos are on the job!
description.56: The Terrible Trio is back and ready to cause mischief!
description.57: The Fantastic Four go back to school! But not to pursue undergraduate studies. When the Dragon Man unleashes chaos on a college campus, will the FF be able to save the co-eds in his path of destruction?
description.59: Who is Patsy Walker's secret new beau? And does this mean she's on the outs with Buzz Baxter?
description.64: Thor meets two groups of children arguing over who is the stronger - Thor or Hulk? Thor tells them the tale of when he battled the Hulk under an enchantment spell.
description.65: Sick of being made to look like a fool, Hitler orders Strucker to defeat Fury and the Howling Commandos once and for all in an elaborate set-up!
description.66: It appears some of the X-Men may be seeing greener pastures as members of the Fantastic Four!
description.68: Super-villain Gideon has pitted the Fantastic team against each other! When your best asset is team-work, what chance do you stand divided? Sibling against sibling, friend against friend!
description.69: Zeus plans a mission for his son Hercules and the Asgardian Thor...in order for the two gods to make amends with each other for good!
description.70: The Scorpion’s first appearance! How can Spidey battle a foe who is stronger than he is?!
description.75: Odin has a change of heart and is touched by his son's fight to save the mortally-wounded Jane Foster! While Thor dukes it out on Earth against his foes, Odin summons a healing potion to be created.
description.76: GUEST STARRING: Captain America and Bucky! The two heroes need a little help from Sgt. Fury and his Commandos to halt an invasion on England.
description.77: Does a power struggle exist within the Fantastic Four? Torch seems to think so...
description.78: A new development for the Fantastic Four! The team joins Namor, the Sub-Mariner, to take down an aquatic foe that is causing trouble in Atlantis. Will Namor have the audacity to flirt with the Invisible Woman in front of Mr. Fantastic?
description.81: Spidey strikes back! Guest-starring the Human Torch and featuring such villains as the Sandman and the Evil Enforcers!
description.87: The end of Spider-Man? Sandman is in town, and Spider-Man is cringing in fear!
description.88: The things we do for love! When Jane Foster is kidnapped by Loki's minions Cobra and Mr. Hyde, Thor will do anything to save her - even if that means disobeying his father, Odin!
description.89: Captain Sawyer has a new mission for Sergeant Fury: locate the buzz-bomb launcher and mark it for a bomber mission that will reach the area at 0300 the next morning!
description.90: The Mad Thinker and the Puppet Master have combined their efforts to outsmart the Fantastic Four!
description.92: Who exactly is the Invincible Man? What beef does he have with the Fantastic Four? And just how invincible is this new villain? A hero will fall in this shocking issue.

5.text: It's always awkward to have relatives crash at your place, especially when they're knocking down the walls! First appearance and origin of Professor X's stepbrother, the Juggernaut!

8.text: Reprinting Journey Into Mystery Annual (1965) #1, available in MU!

9.text: It's Spider-Man versus a super-robot controlled by none other than J. Jonah Jameson!

10.text: The trail suddenly heats up in the search for the Hulk! But can the Avengers trust the information they've received? And can they defeat the Minotaur that stands in their way?

11.text: In the battle of the century, Daredevil must contend with the villainous might of Stilt Man!

21.text: Spider-Man has a sit down with a shrink named Dr. Rinehart. Is Peter Parker going insane?

22.text: Following the consequences of their battle with The Masters of Evil, the Avengers' roster changes dramatically! Who will stay? Who will go? And what new heroes will join the line-up?

26.text: When a common burglar pilfers his latest Iron Man armor, Tony Stark must don his old suit to clear Iron Man's good name. Also: the Red Skull infiltrates the ranks of the US Army, and it's up to Cap & Bucky to bring him to justice!

27.text: Magneto meets his match in the menace called...the Stranger! Can either the X-Men or the Brotherhood withstand his power?

29.text: Hawkeye and a new-and-improved Black Widow return to Tony Stark's neck of the woods with Pepper Potts and Happy Hogan in their sights! Also: a tale from Captain America's dramatic past featuring fortunetelling foes, Sando and Omar!

31.text: Baron Zemo and The Masters of Evil kidnap Rick Jones to draw the Avengers out for an epic battle...but will everyone come out alive?

32.text: What happens when Spidey runs out of web fluid and the Green Goblin empties his bag of tricks? Find out here!

33.text: Daredevil vs. Namor, the Sub-Mariner!  Can DD stop the might of the monarch of the seas?

40.text: Who is the Phantom, and why is he sabotaging Stark International? Also: more of the origin of Captain America is revealed!

42.text: The Wasp is in critical condition! Can the Avengers find Dr. Svenson, the only doctor that can save her, in time?

43.text: Spider-Man deals justice to the Crafty Clown and his Masters of Menace!

47.text: When a trip to the South Pole yields a jungle adventure, the X-Men meet Ka-Zar, lord of the Savage Land!

49.text: It's a battle of good versus evil when Daredevil takes on Mr. Fear and the Fellowship of Fear!

50.text: With Iron Man in his custody, the Mandarin reveals his life story, the origin of his powers, and his plan to ignite World War 3! Also: Captain America must fight his way out of a prison full of pugilistic inmates after his shield is stolen!

52.text: It's Spider-Man and the Human Torch vesus the Beetle!

53.text: In order to put the Avengers out of commission, Count Nefaria puts them up against...themselves?

60.text: With Tony Stark dead to the world after his home is blown to smithereens, it may truly be the end for the Golden Avenger, as the Mandarin has captured him once again! Also: Captain America heads to Vietnam to match the Herculean might of Sumo!

62.text: Ant-Man discovers a nefarious plot being perpetrated underground, so the Avengers must defeat Mole Man to save the earth!

67.text: Where the lethal Lucifer lurks, he must face...the Avengers! But defeating him could destroy the world, so the X-Men must defeat the Avengers instead!

70.text: Another classic Spidey villain makes his debut. Mac Garagan is the Scorpion and he is here to defeat Spider-Man!

71.text: The mighty Avengers meet Spider-Man - but what has become of the armored Avenger Iron Man?

72.text: Daredevil vs. the mysterious Masked Matador!  Ole, DD!

73.text: All but trapped in his armor for fear of his heart giving out, how can Tony Stark prove that he is alive and well without divulging his secret identity as Iron Man? Also: Captain America fights Baron Zemo's Army of Assassins!

81.text: Spidey teams up with the Human Torch and sets the stage for one of the most enduring friendships in the Marvel Universe!

82.text: Immortus, Master of Limbo, begins years of manipulation by joining the Masters of Evil and fragmenting the Avengers! Earth's mightiest heroes battles titans from across time, and nothing is as it seems!

83.text: The Black Knight returns to exact his revenge on the Avengers, but with the rest of the team out of town and his chest device malfunctioning, will Iron Man be able to stop him alone? Also: Captain America must save Jarvis from Bull and his gang!

87.text: Can Spidey live down the shameful events of his last encounter with the Green Goblin? And what does Johnny Storm of the Fantastic Four have to say to Spider-Man?

91.text: Fed up with ungrateful homo sapiens, the Beast leaves the X-Men to enter the wrestling ring! Too bad he finds Unus the Untouchable waiting to knock him down without lifting a finger!

93.text: Why is Iron Man engaged in mortal combat with fellow Avenger Captain America? And what damage will have been wrought by the time the Golden Avenger realizes he's been deceived?

94.text: The Hulk battles an indestructible robot!  Will metal be able to contain a gamma-radiated beast?

95.text: Immortus, Master of Limbo, begins years of manipulation by joining the Masters of Evil and fragmenting the Avengers! Earth's mightiest heroes battles titans from across time, and nothing is as it seems!
Presenting the first appearance of Simon Williams, Wonder Man! Is he the first infiltrator to betray the Avengers, the first Avenger to die in action, or both?
